    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en-US">2-D shape resembling wings or wing-like structures</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en-US">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'aliform' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'shape2 d'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0002236.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en-US">Shape2D(x) ← Aliform(x)</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
