    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001251"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en-US">Color hue denoting darker shades of grey, commonly perceived as neutral</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en-US">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'dark grey' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'grey'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001251.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
