    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0002289"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en-US">Setose is a hairy quality inhering in a bearer due to being covered with setae</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en-US">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'setose' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'hairy'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0002289.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en-US">Hairy(x) ← Setose(x)</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en-US">if x is a &apos;setose&apos; then x is a &apos;hairy&apos;</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:example xml:lang="en-US">Example of a &apos;setose&apos;.</skos:example>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Serous">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/MorphologicalComposition"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en-US">serous</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">serös</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0002128"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en-US">Serous is a composition quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of containing or resembling serum</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en-US">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'serous' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'Morphological composition'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0002128.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en-US">MorphologicalComposition(x) ← Serous(x)</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en-US">if x is a &apos;serous&apos; then x is a &apos;morphological composition&apos;</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:example xml:lang="en-US">Example of a &apos;serous&apos;.</skos:example>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Straggling">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/IrregularSpatialPattern"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en-US">straggling</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">zerstreuert</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001616"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en-US">Irregular spatial pattern exhibiting spreading or sprawling growth</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en-US">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'straggling' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'irregular spatial pattern'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001616.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en-US">IrregularSpatialPattern(x) ← Straggling(x)</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en-US">if x is a &apos;straggling&apos; then x is a &apos;irregular spatial pattern&apos;</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:example xml:lang="en-US">Example of a &apos;straggling&apos;.</skos:example>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Waxy">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Waxiness"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">wachsartig</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en-US">waxy</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0002384"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en-US">Waxy is a quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the presence of long chain aliphatic lipids on the surface of an organism</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en-US">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'waxy' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'waxiness'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0002384.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en-US">Waxiness(x) ← Waxy(x)</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en-US">if x is a &apos;waxy&apos; then x is a &apos;waxiness&apos;</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:example xml:lang="en-US">Example of a &apos;waxy&apos;.</skos:example>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Spindly">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Slender"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="de">spindeldürr</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en-US">spindly</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0002321"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en-US">Slender quality characterized by having an elongated, thin appearance, often lacking robustness</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en-US">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'spindly' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'slender'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0002321.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en-US">Slender(x) ← Spindly(x)</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en-US">if x is a &apos;spindly&apos; then x is a &apos;slender&apos;</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:example xml:lang="en-US">Example of a &apos;spindly&apos;.</skos:example>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Subovoid">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Spheroid"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en-US">subovoid</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:adaptedFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0002537"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en-US">Spheroid form resembling an elongated oval but less defined, slightly asymmetrical</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en-US">Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'subovoid' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'spheroid'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0002537.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en-US">Spheroid(x) ← Subovoid(x)</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en-US">if x is a &apos;subovoid&apos; then x is a &apos;spheroid&apos;</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:example xml:lang="en-US">Example of a &apos;subovoid&apos;.</skos:example>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Morphological/Auriculate">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
